  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no credible evidence or verified information indicating that Khizr Khan was paid over $100,000 by CNN and NBC or $175,000 by the Democratic National Committee (DNC). \n\nKhizr Khan gained national attention for his impactful speech at the 2016 Democratic National Convention, where he spoke about his late son, Captain Humayun Khan, who was killed in Iraq in 2004, and criticized then-presidential candidate Donald Trump's policies regarding Muslims and immigrants. While his speech resonated with many and led to various media appearances and speaking engagements, specific financial compensation details from major news networks like CNN and NBC, or from political organizations like the DNC, have not been substantiated through reputable sources.\n\nIt's important to approach such claims critically and verify them through reliable news outlets or official statements. Misinformation can often circulate online, so ensuring the credibility of the sources is crucial. If you encountered these claims in a specific context or platform, I recommend checking the information against trustworthy news organizations or official disclosures.",
